commText: de Kock and Rahul are at the crease. de Kock is on strike. Topley will open the attack
Topley to de Kock, no run, oh that's very gentle from Topley, just 127.5kph on this length ball outswinger, de Kock defends towards cover
Topley to de Kock, no run, beaten! Good length delivery swinging away outside off stump, de Kock swings hard and misses

Topley to de Kock, FOUR, top edgeee and it almost goes all the way! Short delivery that's outside off stump, de Kock swings hard, gets a thick edge that's comfortably over the cordon. First runs for him

Topley to de Kock, no run, oh a wild play and miss! Wonder what's the plan from RCB about. QdK is so strong on the pull but seems like they want to make him fetch it from well outside off stump for a top edge. Luckily for the batter he missed it completely as he looked surprised by some spongy bounce
Topley to de Kock, FOUR, now Topley goes for the bluff with a really full delivery but de Kock is ready for a neat cover-drive for four

Topley to de Kock, FOUR, they have point very open and point is a strong zone for Quinton! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, de Kock stays leg-side and punches it square for a racy boundary. Turns out to be a great start for LSG
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yash Dayal to Rahul, no run, oh cracking shot and a cracking diving effort at short cover! Full and in the slot, Rahul leans into the drive and smacks it, great effort by Kohli denies a certain four
Yash Dayal to Rahul, 1 run, inswinging length delivery, Rahul works it through backward square leg
Yash Dayal to de Kock, FOUR, oh freebie full and outside off stump, de Kock leans forward, doesn't hit it hard just places the drive wide of cover-point for four more
RCB have gone to both left-arm pacers because both KL and QdK are susceptible to this variety of bowling and this meant they have sacrificed Siraj with new ball
Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, outside off stump, de Kock lets it pass
Yash Dayal to de Kock, 1 run, width outside off stump, de Kock cuts past point, fielder doesn't cut it off and they get a run
Yash Dayal to Rahul, 1 run, short of length delivery finishing leg-side, easy glance through backward square leg for KL
They have gone to Siraj now
Mohammed Siraj, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Siraj to Rahul, no run, beats him on the outside edge! 140.kph full delivery wide of off stump, gentle away movement, KL played a loose drive and missed. Though it was 140 it looked like KL had so much time
Mohd Siraj in IPL \nOpening bowling: Avg 25.78 | ER 7.98 | SR 19.3 \nAs change bowler: Avg 42.00 | ER 9.72 | SR 25.9
Siraj to Rahul, 1 run, punchy push through point for a run

Siraj to de Kock, no run, leading edgee doesn't carry. Siraj a master of nipping the ball away and across the left-handers, Quinton was early into the flick, bat faced closed and he was very lucky it didn't have the legs to carry to mid-off

Siraj to de Kock, SIX, do not bowl on the pads to Quinton de Kock will be the first message to bowlers in a team meeting. Siraj runs in with intent and fires a leg-side freebie, out comes the pick up flick and he clears fine leg easily

Siraj to de Kock, SIX, and again! This is poor from Siraj. Successive balls on the pads and this time de Kock flicks over deep square leg for six more to silence the crowd again. Quinton is looking dangerous. Where's Maxwell?
Siraj to de Kock, no run, yorker, good comeback, de Kock digs it out
Here's Maxi for QdK but will this be KL's chance?
Glenn Maxwell, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Maxwell to Rahul, wide, turn but down leg, KL misses the glance. Good take down leg
Maxwell to Rahul, 1 run, nudge to mid-on and RCB have what they wanted - off-spin to Quinton
Maxwell to de Kock, 1 run, just a straight-batted push towards mid-off as Maxwell slows it up from round the wicket
Maxwell to Rahul, no run, backs away and exposes the sticks, Rahul manages to punch this non-turner to cover
Maxwell to Rahul, no run, troubled him by shortening his length as he stepped out, rushed defence to the off-side
Maxwell to Rahul, 1 run, quick on the stumps, KL nudges it to short mid-wicket
Faf has a message for Maxi
Maxwell to de Kock, no run, flat and on the stumps, de Kock flicks gently towards backward square leg. A quiet over from Maxi. Can the bowler at the other end keep it tight and add pressure?
Yash Dayal [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Rahul, 1 run, length delivery on the off stump, KL happily pushes to mid-off and says, over to you, Quinny
Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, ah well bowled! Quinton early into a pre-determined leg-side scoop, Yash Dayal took pace off to sneak this under the bat

Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, ohh massive attempt for a lofted cover drive but got beaten by late away movement. Full and looked like a slot ball, so Quinton went real hard at it, got done in by a grassy patch

Yash Dayal to de Kock, 1 run, under edge rolls to short third man. Outstanding slower ball bumper and the key was outside off stump to make the batter fetch, could so easily have been a skier for the keeper or short third

Yash Dayal to Rahul, SIX, KL tees off finally! Yash Dayal added so much pressure but he goes for the glory full inswinger from round the wicket, it did swing nicely but KL was ready and showed his class with a straight lofted drive

Yash Dayal to Rahul, 2 runs, oh he gets away with a hack! Slot ball, KL moved across for a slog, toe-ended that high and it plugged close to long-on and slows down. Yash Dayal fails to close out that over nicely after a great start
Maxwell to de Kock, 1 run, flatter delivery on the off stump, de Kock works it to square leg

Maxwell to Rahul, SIX, in the airrrrr, palmed over the rope! Patidar the man didn't time his jump better. Full and down leg - the bait with deep backward square leg in place - KL slog-sweeps flat. Patidar runs to his right and jumps but fails to cling on
Maxwell to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maxwell to Rahul, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Mistimed high and taken at cover. This is a massive wicket for RCB. They brought on Maxi to get Quinton but they have got the big fish. KL tried to maximize on a short ball, but this seems to have jumped extra and the pull shot was a complete mishit. RCB fans find their voices again. Actually was rushed on the shot a bit. Rahul c Mayank Dagar b Maxwell 20(14) [6s-2]
Devdutt Padikkal, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell to Padikkal, no run, flatter delivery on the off stump, Padikkal punches it to the off-side
Maxwell to Padikkal, no run, tight on the off stump, Padikkal plays towards cover-point

Maxwell to Padikkal, 1 run, mistimed hit but safe! Again Maxwell dangles a leg-side full delivery with a catching man at deep backward square leg, Padikkal gets a top-edgish sweep out, luckily it landed to the left of the rushing fielder. Maxi and the crowd almost thought they had two in the over

Highlights (1-6 overs) - de Kock is off and running with three fours in the first over - Siraj does not open the bowling, comes on in the 3rd over - de Kock smashes Siraj for 2 sixes - Maxwell bowls a quiet over, just 4 runs - Rahul smacks his first six off Dayal - Patidar parries Rahul's slog sweep over the rope, tough chance - Maxwell breaks the 53-run opening stand, Rahul departs
Reece Topley [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Topley to Padikkal, 1 run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Padikkal dabs to third man

Topley to de Kock, 2 runs, oh mishit, mishit and Maxi doesn't hold on! Full and outside off stump, de Kock plays a wild lofted shot, toe-ends it high over mid-off, Maxi runs back from mid-off, seemed like he had in control but slowed down for a wee bit, then stretched forward and wasn't in control at all
50-50 powerplay that. RCB pulled things back with the wicket of KL and 54 isn't a big deal in the PP at the Chinnaswamy
Topley to de Kock, no run, oh another blind slog from de Kock, only to miss it completely! Length delivery outside off stump, de Kock goes hard for a another hit and totally misses it
Topley to de Kock, 1 run, slower short delivery, de Kock pulls it to deep mid-wicket
Topley to Padikkal, no run, beaten! More like the Topley we have seen. Hard length into the wicket, seaming away with bounce, Padikkal poked at it off the back foot and misses
Fewest innings to 3000 IPL runs 75 C Gayle 80 KL Rahul 85 J Buttler 94 D Warner/ Faf du Plessis 99 Q de Kock*
Topley to Padikkal, 1 run, short of length delivery, Padikkal dabs it to third man. Just 5 off that over
Maxwell to Padikkal, 1 run, full and on the stumps, Padikkal leans forward and drives to long-off
Maxwell to de Kock, 1 run, goes deep in the crease and flicks wide of mid-on, looks for two but wasn't there
Maxwell to Padikkal, no run, oh DDP wanted a big slog-sweep, missed it and got hit on the pad down leg
Maxwell to Padikkal, 1 run, quick and on the leg stump, Padikkal works it to the on-side
Maxwell to de Kock, no run, quick on the off stump, de Kock goes back and punches it to point

Maxwell to de Kock, no run, appeal for LBW, height the issue. Slider on the stumps, de Kock looks to flick, misses, impact in line with middle but looked high and RCB don't chance the review. Hawkeye confirms impact on middle and leg and bouncing over leg stump. Anuj Rawat too was suggesting height when they were discussing the review

Timeout. RCB have done really well to tighten the screwss - just 16 off the last 3 overs with a wicket and a few chances and one over was inside the PP too. Pressure on LSG who need to be careful of not aiming too high on a pitch that's not straightforward for batting as of now. Maxi has already finished 3 and LSG would be mindful of looting runs at the end. 190 seems a good score on this pitch without dew
Mohammed Siraj [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Siraj to Padikkal, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Padikkal works it to the on-side
Siraj to de Kock, no run, play and miss! Short delivery angling across, it's clear they want to make him fetch the pull and the batter misses

Siraj to de Kock, SIX, the moment Siraj gets the short ball close to the body it disappears over the leg-side. Short delivery outside off stump, de Kock gets slightly closer to the ball and muscles it flat over mid-wicket
Siraj to de Kock, 1 run, low full toss, de Kock guides it to deep backward point
Siraj to Padikkal, wide, bumper too high from Siraj
Siraj to Padikkal, wide, oh a high full toss down leg, could have hit DDP had he stayed put. Sure he missed an easy tickle for four there
Siraj to Padikkal, wide, good slower bumper outside off stump but it's too high again says the ump. Siraj can't believe it's a wide. Are they going to review, no!
Siraj to Padikkal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Padikkal, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! This is what they were trying to do all day. To bowl short at the LHBs and make them fetch the pull shot for a top edge, finally it's paid off, thanks to a brilliant catch running back by the keeper. Give this to the fielder I say. Short delivery angling across, Padikkal looks to pull, big top edge that only has height, keeper runs back, third man runs in, keeper says mine and somehow clings on with both hands and makes it look simple. DDP's poor start to the IPL continues. Padikkal c Anuj Rawat b Siraj 6(11)
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Stoinis, no run, short of length delivery, Stoinis defends off the back foot
Now RCB are dangling the carrot to Quinton with left-arm spin. Should be fun if the bowler can hold the nerve
Mayank Dagar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, 5 wides, oh dear! He's fired this down leg with fear and no chance for the keeper
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, 1 run, shortish and outside off stump, de Kock cuts square of the wicket to deep point
Stoinis v left arm spin - RCB will love this
Mayank Dagar to Stoinis, 1 run, but he gets off strike immediately with a drive to long-off
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, 1 run, looks like he's going to bowl wide of off and outside de Kock's arc. Short delivery, cuts to the off-side, lovely diving save at backward point
Mayank Dagar to Stoinis, 1 run, inside-edge slog rolls along the ground to deep mid-wicket
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, 1 run, now he bowls on the pads and Quinton is kind enough to flick through backward square leg just for a run
Mayank Dagar to Stoinis, 1 run, lovely turn but the ball was too full and Stoinis played a comfortable off-drive to long-off
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Green to Stoinis, FOUR, low full toss down leg, Stoinis flicks and accepts the gift gleefully! Races away through backward square leg
Green to Stoinis, no run, oh had to adjust to the extra bounce from back of a length and change his leg-side attempt to a back foot defence
Green to Stoinis, 1 run, this is smart! Moves across and flicks this slowish delivery past short fine but it's just one because Siraj is fine at long leg
Green to de Kock, no run, moves in the crease for a big hit, pace off and angling across wide of off, de Kock slashes and misses
Green to de Kock, no run, beaten again! Full and angling away, length-wise it's slot but the line is tough for the left-hander when he tried to hit down the ground and completely missed it
Green to de Kock, 1 run, full delivery, de Kock swings too hard, fielded at mid-off. Good over despite a boundary first ball
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, 1 run, oh he's managed to land this mistimed lofted hit between long-off and extra-cover. Backed away and tried to loft this down the ground, toe-ender
Mayank Dagar to Stoinis, no run, flighted delivery on the leg stump, Stoinis defends
Mayank Dagar to Stoinis, 1 run, leg-side flighted delivery, glanced to short fine leg

Mayank Dagar to de Kock, FOUR, de Kock plays a wild smack down the ground, beats the outstretched arm of the bowler and long-off had no chance. Flat-batted straight for a 22nd IPL fifty. Started off so well but slowed down as RCB bowled smartly. LSG applaud his effort. Can he maximize his stay?
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, no run, clever wide flatter delivery just inside the line, de Kock let it go but it wasn't a wide
Mayank Dagar to de Kock, SIX, oh he's overpitched and made the over look poor. QdK says that's what I was looking for and smacks it straight down the ground this time all the way

Highlights (7-12 overs) - Maxwell drops QdK on 32, Topley the unlucky bowler - QdK breaks the shackles by hammering Siraj over the rope - Siraj bowls three wides before accounting for Padikkal - Dagar starts off his spell with 5 wides - Green starts his spell with a four but only concedes 6 runs - Consecutive fifties for QdK, comes off 36 balls
Green to Stoinis, 1 run, full toss, Stoinis drills the drive, cut off to the left of mid-off
Green to de Kock, SIX, full toss and de Kock just slices the drive over point. The shot of the innings so far. Didn't try to overhit either. Just opened the bat face last second and stole a six
Green to de Kock, 1 run, sets base for a slog, de Kock drills it to long-on
Green to Stoinis, SIX, another full toss! This is poor bowling. Stoinis happily smashes this over mid-wicket. A mishit by his standards but he clears the rope easily
Green to Stoinis, 1 run, pace off on this short of length delivery, Stoinis taps it to cover-point
Green to de Kock, FOUR, make that 19 off that really poor over filled with full tosses or overcooked stuff. This is full and in the slot, de Kock lofts over cover and milks more out of this over
Glenn Maxwell [3.0-0-15-1] is back into the attack
Maxwell to Stoinis, SIX, LSG have got back the momentum. Maxwell comes on and feeds it in the slot, Stoinis clears his front leg and launches it over wide long-on. RCB bowlers under pressure now..
Maxwell to Stoinis, 1 run, flatter and bowled into the wicket, Stoinis knocks it to long-off
Round the wicket to de Kock
Maxwell to de Kock, no run, drifts in with the angle, de Kock blocks it back to Maxwell
Maxwell to de Kock, 1 run, slower and around off, de Kock nurdles it backward of square leg. He's happy to see off Maxwell..
Maxwell to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Maxwell to Stoinis, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Second wicket for Maxwell. And once again it is the right hander he accounts for. Stoinis is disappointed as he starts the walk back. This was the half tracker and he wanted to smash it out of the ground, once more the ball bounces a tad more and he ends up slicing it over point, Dagar runs back from backward point and takes a good catch. Stoinis c Mayank Dagar b Maxwell 24(15) [4s-1 6s-2]
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Maxwell to Pooran, no run, pushed through on off, Pooran eases it to the off-side and sees off Maxwell's spell. He finishes with figures of 4-0-23-2
Yash Dayal [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, I0$ yorker outside off, de Kock lets it pass and the ball is within the wide marker
Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, now the slower ball at I0$, de Kock is deceived for pace and fails to lay bat on ball
Yash Dayal to de Kock, 1 run, I0$ very full and outside off, de Kock jams it square of the wicket
Yash Dayal to Pooran, 1 run, wide yorker outside off and Pooran slices it to deep backward point. Dayal bowling to his field..

RCB review! Not sure if it is for a wide or a caught behind. Anuj Rawat wasn't sure if there was some glove. The umpire signaled wide as well. It is for a wide check.. "The ball has not gone over his head if he stood up," says the third umpire.

Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, that's a good call to review. RCB save a run. Slower bouncer around leg-stump, de Kock takes on the pull and fails to connect. The ball flies over the glove or bat. The height was not a problem as it was head high
Yash Dayal to de Kock, no run, yorker outside off, the batter doesn't lay bat on ball
Mohammed Siraj [2.0-0-24-1] is back into the attack
Siraj to Pooran, 1 run, angled across the left hander, Pooran dabs it to backward point and crosses over
Siraj to de Kock, no run, low full toss outside off, de Kock drills the drive straight to mid-off and Faf gets his body behind to make the stop

Siraj to de Kock, FOUR, full pitcher outside off, de Kock this time manages to beat Faf. He drives it straight of mid-off and Faf runs across to his left, dives and the ball still beats him. Siraj is down on his knees
Siraj to de Kock, no run, slower short ball angled across, de Kock tries to fetch the pull but does not make contact

Siraj to de Kock, FOUR, in the air and over mid-off. Poor planning and execution from Siraj. He's pitching 'em up with mid-off inside the ring, just a free swing of the bat for de Kock and he manages to evade a leaping Faf
Siraj to de Kock, 1 run, full toss on leg-stump, de Kock flicks it to deep mid-wicket and retains strike

Timeout! RCB have been so inconsistent. Their 5th bowler quota went for 49 runs in 4 overs. Not sure it was wise to bowl Dagar and Green for four successive overs. That allowed de Kock and Stoinis scored quickly and LSG had the impetus. Maxwell broke that partnership and Dayal followed up with a tight over, only for Siraj to come back and release the pressure.

Highlights (13-16 overs) - Green leaks 19 runs to lift the LSG camp - Stoinis smacks Maxwell but the latter has him caught same over - Yash Dayal bowls a momentum-killing 2-run over - Siraj bowl two full slot balls with mid-off to release pressure
Reece Topley [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Topley to de Kock, no run, I0$ yorker around off, de Kock swings early and the ball sneaks under his bat
Topley to de Kock, 1 run, high full toss below the waist, de Kock flat-bats it wide of deep mid-wicket and Kohli keeps it to a single

Topley to Pooran, 1 run, dropped! Tough chance but Anuj Rawat with gloves on should be taking that. How costly a miss would this turn out? It is Pooran. Back of the hand slower ball and Pooran did not pick it, swings across the line and gets a massive top-edge towards square leg, Rawat calls for it and runs forward, Dayal was also there but he left it to the keeper, Rawat dived forward and did not manage to hang on
Topley to de Kock, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Topley to de Kock, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Should have been two in two. But RCB will settle with the set batter walking back. de Kock would be livid with himself. This was a juicy full toss outside off, de Kock gets no timing or the middle as he looks to loft down the ground, in fact the bat turns on impact and the miscue is held near long-off. Not a fluent knock but he kept picking the boundaries when needed. de Kock c Mayank Dagar b Topley 81(56) [4s-8 6s-5]
Q de Kock innings tonight \nvs Siraj: 28 off 12 (SR 233.33) \nvs rest: 53 off 44 (SR 120.45)
Ayush Badoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Topley to Ayush Badoni, no run, slower ball on middle and leg, Badoni gently turns it to mid-wicket
Topley to Ayush Badoni, no run, good length ball and Badoni goes for the big heave, mistimed to mid-wicket
Dayal, Topley and Siraj have an over each.. They should be the trio finishing off the innings
Yash Dayal [3.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack

Yash Dayal to Pooran, FOUR, crunched! Dayal misses his yorker by a couple of inches or so, Pooran opens the bat face and drives it square. There was a deep backward point and deep extra cover, but he placed it between them
Yash Dayal to Pooran, no run, slower ball bowled into the wicket, Pooran shuffles across and toe-ends it back to Dayal
Yash Dayal to Pooran, no run, I0$ short of length delivery, Pooran is early into the pull and is struck on the back

Yash Dayal to Pooran, no run, I0$ low full toss outside off, Pooran jams it into the off-side and Dayal prevents the quick single. He's pulled it back nicely after the first ball four. Can he finish well?
Yash Dayal to Pooran, 1 run, I0$ off-pace delivery and Pooran mistimes the loft to long-off
Yash Dayal to Ayush Badoni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by du Plessis!! That's an excellent catch by Faf. Maxwell dropped a similar one early in the game and he's the first one there to embrace Faf. Slower ball banged into the surface, Badoni fetches it from outside off and toe-ends the slap over extra cover, Faf runs back and puts in the dive to hang on. He went with both hands and ensured he had the ball in control even after hitting the ground. Ayush Badoni c du Plessis b Yash Dayal 0(3)
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Topley to Pooran, no run, I0$ wide yorker outside off, Pooran lets it pass and it is just inside the marker
Topley to Pooran, wide, this time Topley sprays it well beyond the marker, Pooran gets his wide

Topley to Pooran, SIX, wow! That ball barely left the ground. Second time a full toss is sent over the point rope. This was just below the waist and Pooran could get under it easily, he opens the bat face and slices it just over the rope

Topley to Pooran, SIX, two in two. Replay of the previous ball. Why is Topley going for the yorker? He troubled Pooran with his slower ball in the previous over. Another high full toss and Pooran is not missing out, slashes it into the point stand
100th IPL six for Pooran in 62 innings

Topley to Pooran, SIX, that's landed on the roof. Hat-trick of sixes and Pooran is turning it on, making RCB pay for the dropped catch. Slower ball but this one is short and sits up, Pooran waits on the back foot and hammers it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball lands on the roof and goes out of the ground
LSG review! It is for a wide and the third umpire needed just one replay. It will be a fair delivery..
Topley to Pooran, no run, full and outside off, this was in the slot and Pooran threw the kitchen sink, fails to connect and the ball was inside the wide marker. He took a chance and wasted a review
Topley to Pooran, 1 run, low full toss around off, Pooran goes hard on the drive and mistimes to long-on. But he will retain strike..
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-34-1] is back into the attack
Siraj to Pooran, no run, yorker outside off, Pooran fails to connect as the ball sneaks under his willow

Siraj to Pooran, no run, once again Pooran has reviewed. It is for a non-wide call outside off. Don't think he's getting this either. The original decision is withheld. Full and angled outside off, Pooran swings off his feet and does not make contact. The ball was inside the wide marker and Pooran wastes both reviews

Siraj to Pooran, no run, now the bouncer which takes Pooran by surprise, he was ducking and at the same time trying to play the pull, but the ball flies over his blade and it is one for the over signals the umpire
Siraj to Pooran, SIX, this time Pooran connects. Full and slanted outside off, he reaches with an open face and slices it over deep backward point

Siraj to Pooran, SIX, it is six or nothing for Pooran. He was waiting for the short ball, this is the slower one bowled into the wicket, gets into position quickly and whacks it into the deep mid-wicket stand
Siraj to Pooran, 1 run, missed out there. Full toss outside off, Pooran mistimes the drive to long-off and has to settle with a single

21:10 Local Time, 15:40 GMT: This is an excellent total from Lucknow Super Giants. The surface is two-paced and the ball is not coming on. So it won't be a straightforward chase for Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Quinton de Kock got off to a flier and added a 50+ stand with skipper Rahul. LSG lost a bit of momentum after the powerplay but RCB handed it back by bowling Dagar and Green for 4 consecutive overs. de Kock and Stoinis made the most of that move and a smashed 50+ partnership in quick time. Maxwell broke that stand and it seemed RCB were pulling things back, but Pooran was dropped in the 17th over by Rawat and he made them pay by smashing 5 sixes in the last two overs to take LSG past the 180-mark. Over to Kohli and Co. for the chase..

Pooran's balls/six ratio is bettered only by Russell among the 36 players with 100+ sixes in IPL. 6.6 A Russell (200 sixes) 8.6 N Pooran (103) 9.3 C Gayle (357) 10.4 K Pollard (223) 11.0 G Maxwell (159)
Pooran at Chinnaswamy (IPL) 46(28) 62(19) 40*(21) 68 balls | 148 runs | SR 217.64 | 17 sixes (a six every four balls)

Glenn Maxwell: Plan was to keep it simple and wait for a mistake. Probably going to be a tough chase because it's (bounce) a bit inconsistent, we have to be at our best. I felt like we gave a lot of easy boundaries at the start and wanted to get a bit of energy and a wicket. Dropped catches cost us. I think it's two paced so we have to be at our best. Hopefully the ones who get starts can go on.

Welcome back.. Lucknow Super Giants have activated their impact sub - Quinton de Kock goes out, Siddarth comes on. Kohli and Faf are out in the middle. RCB need their skipper to step up today. Siddarth straightaway will start proceedings. KL Rahul has the gloves. Wide deep sleep in place. We are ready to go..
